# Package Management Rules

## Yarn Only
- **ALWAYS use yarn** for package management, never npm
- Use `yarn add` instead of `npm install`
- Use `yarn remove` instead of `npm uninstall`
- Use `yarn` instead of `npm run`
- Use `yarn add --dev` for development dependencies

## Examples
```bash
# ✅ Correct
yarn add cuid
yarn add --dev @types/node
yarn remove lodash
yarn dev

# ❌ Incorrect
npm install cuid
npm install --save-dev @types/node
npm uninstall lodash
npm run dev
```

## Lock File Management
- Always commit `yarn.lock` to version control
- Never commit `package-lock.json` (delete if present)
- Use `yarn install` to install dependencies from lock file